2)(L), (M). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/118/272"},"text":"Pub. L. 118–272","children":[],"tail":" added subpars. (L) and (M)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2022—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/s8103/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, § 8103(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Shoreline and riverine protection and restoration” for “Flood mitigation and riverine restoration program” in section catchline."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/s8103/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, § 8103(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (a) and struck out former subsec. (a). Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “The Secretary may undertake a program for the purpose of conducting projects to reduce flood hazards and restore the natural functions and values of rivers throughout the United States.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/s8103/a/3/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, § 8103(a)(3)(A)","children":[],"tail":" added par. (1) and struck out former par. (1). Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “In carrying out the program, the Secretary may conduct studies to identify appropriate flood damage reduction, conservation, and restoration measures and may design and implement projects described in subsection (a).”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/s8103/a/3/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, § 8103(a)(3)(B)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “flood and hurricane and storm damages, including the use of natural features or nature-based features” for “flood damages”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/s8103/a/3/C"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, § 8103(a)(3)(C)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “and hurricane and storm” after “flood”, “, shoreline,” after “riverine”, and “and coastal barriers” after “floodplains”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/s8103/a/4/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, § 8103(a)(4)(A)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “, except that the first $200,000 of the costs of a study conducted under this section shall be at Federal expense” before period at end."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/s8103/a/4/B/i"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, § 8103(a)(4)(B)(i)","children":[],"tail":", struck out “flood control” after “nonstructural” in heading."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(2)(A). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/s8103/a/4/B/ii"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, § 8103(a)(4)(B)(ii)","children":[],"tail":", added subpar. (A) and struck out former subpar. (A). Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “The non-Federal interests shall pay 35 percent of the cost of any environmental restoration or nonstructural flood control project carried out under this section.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/s8103/a/4/C"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, § 8103(a)(4)(C)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “or hurricane and storm damage reduction” after “flood control” in heading and text, and substituted “"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t33/s2213"},"text":"section 2213 of this title","children":[],"tail":", except that the non-Federal share of the cost to design and construct such a project benefitting an economically disadvantaged community (including economically disadvantaged communities located in urban and rural areas) shall be 10 percent” for “"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t33/s2213/a"},"text":"section 2213(a) of this title","children":[],"tail":"” in text."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/s8103/a/5"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, § 8103(a)(5)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (d) and struck out former subsec. (d) which related to project justification."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/s8103/a/6"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, § 8103(a)(6)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Areas for Examination” for “Priority areas” in subsec. heading, designated existing provisions as par. (1) and inserted par. heading, redesignated former pars. (1) to (33) as subpars. (A) to (GG), respectively, of par. (1) and realigned margins, and added par. (2)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (f). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/s8103/a/7"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, § 8103(a)(7)","children":[],"tail":", (8), redesignated subsec. (h) as (f) and struck out former subsec. (f) which related to program review."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (f)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/s8103/a/9"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, § 8103(a)(9)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (2) and struck out former par. (2) which related to projects exceeding $15,000,000."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (g). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/s8103/a/7"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, § 8103(a)(7)","children":[],"tail":", (10), added subsec. (g) and struck out former subsec. (g). Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “Not more than $30,000,000 may be expended by the United States on any single project under this section.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (h). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/s8103/a/8"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, § 8103(a)(8)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated subsec. (h) as (f)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (i). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/s8103/a/7"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, § 8103(a)(7)","children":[],"tail":", struck out subsec. (i) which related to authorization of appropriations."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2007—Subsec. (e)(23). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/114/s5005/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–114, § 5005(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", struck out “and” at end."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (e)(29) to (33). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/114/s5005/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–114, § 5005(a)","children":[],"tail":", added pars. (29) to (33)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (i)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/114/s5005/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–114, § 5005(b)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “section $20,000,000” for “section—"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(A) $20,000,000 for fiscal year 2001;","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(B) $30,000,000 for fiscal year 2002; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(C) $50,000,000 for each of fiscal years 2003 through 2005”.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2000—Subsec. (e)(24) to (28). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/541"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–541","children":[],"tail":" added pars. (24) to (28)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id6c5bcf30-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"transferOfFunctions","id":"id6c5bcf31-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For transfer of all functions, personnel, assets, components, authorities, grant programs, and liabilities of the Federal Emergency Management Agency, including the functions of the Under Secretary for Federal Emergency Management relating thereto, to the Federal Emergency Management Agency, see ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t6/s315/a/1"},"text":"section 315(a)(1) of Title 6","children":[],"tail":", Domestic Security."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For transfer of functions, personnel, assets, and liabilities of the Federal Emergency Management Agency, including the functions of the Director of the Federal Emergency Management Agency relating thereto, to the Secretary of Homeland Security, and for treatment of related references, see former section 313(1) and sections 551(d), 552(d), and 557 of Title 6, Domestic Security, and the Department of Homeland Security Reorganization Plan of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-11-25"},"text":"November 25, 2002","children":[],"tail":", as modified, set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t6/s542"},"text":"section 542 of Title 6","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id6c5bcf32-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"“Secretary” Defined","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Secretary means the Secretary of the Army, see ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/53/s2"},"text":"section 2 of Pub. L. 106–53","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t33/s2201"},"text":"section 2201 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
